Inkompatibel overstyring. A function marked override must exactly match the parameter and return type declaration of the function it is overriding. It must have the same number of parameters, each of the same type, and declare the same return type. If any of the parameters are optional, that must match as well. Both functions must use the same access specifier (public, private, and so on) or namespace attribute as well.

Overstyrer en funksjon som ikke er merket for overstyring. If a method in a class overrides a method in a base class, you must explicitly declare it by using the override attribute, as this example shows:

Kan ikke omdefinere en final-metode. The method cannot be extended because it is marked as final in the base class.

Funksjoner kan ikke være både static og virtual.
Funksjoner kan ikke være både final og virtual.

Finner ikke typen, eller så er den ikke en konstant under kompilering: %s. The class used as a type declaration is either unknown or is an expression that could have different values at run time. Check that you are importing the correct class and that its package location has not changed. Also, check that the package that contains the code (not the imported class) is defined correctly (for example, make sure to use proper ActionScript 3.0 package syntax, and not ActionScript 2.0 syntax).

The error can also occur if the class being referenced is not defined in a namespace that is in use or is not defined as public:

public class Foo{}

If you are using Flex™ Builder™ 2 and the class is in a library, make sure to set the class path for the project.

Initialisering for parameter ukjent, eller så er den ikke en konstant under kompilering.
The value used as the default value for the parameter is either undefined or could have different values at run time. Check that the initializer is spelled correctly, and that the initializer value isn't an expression that could result in different possible values at run time.
Ugyldig tilordning til en variabel som er angitt som en konstant.
Kan ikke tilordne en verdi som ikke er en referanse.
Returverdien må være udefinert. You are attempting to use the return statement within a method that has a declared return type void.

Initialisering for konstant er ukjent, eller så er den ikke en konstant under kompilering.
The value used to initialize the constant is either undefined or could have different values at run time. Check that the initializer is spelled correctly, and that the initializer value isn't an expression that could result in different possible values at run time.
Aksessortyper må stemme overens.

Returtype for en setterdefinisjon må være uspesifisert eller tom. You cannot specify a return value for a setter function. For example, the following is invalid: 
public function set gamma(g:Number):Number;

The following is valid:

public function set gamma(g:Number):void;
Egenskapen er skrivebeskyttet.

Egenskapen er skrivebeskyttet. This property is defined through a getter function, which allows you to retrieve that property's value. There is no setter function defined for this property, however, so it is read-only.

In the following example, line 3 generates an error because there is no setter function defined for xx: 

class D { function get xx() { return 22; } }
var d:D = new D();
d.xx = 44; // error, property is read-only

public int z;// should be 'public var z:int;'
This error might also occur when the compiler encounters an unexpected character. For example, the following use of the trace() function is invalid, because of the missing parentheses (the correct syntax is trace("hello")): 
trace "hello"

Syntaksfeil: forventer xml før navneområde. The correct statement syntax is default xml namespace = ns. Either the keyword xml (note the lowercase) is missing or an incorrect keyword was used. For more information, see the default xml namespace directive.

Mulig uendelig rekursjon som skyldes denne filen, inkluderer: %s. A file that is included in the source being compiled contains other include statements that would cause an infinite loop. For example, the following files. a.as and b.as, generate this error because each file tries to include the other.

File a.as contains the following, which attempts to include the file b.as: 

import foo.bar.baz;
include "b.as"
trace(2);

File b.as contains the following, which attempts to include the file a.as: 

include "a.as"

Referanse med sirkulær type funnet i %s. A class is trying to extend a superclass. For example, class A cannot extend class B if B inherits from A: 
class a extends b { }
class b extends a { }
Attributtet public kan kun brukes i en pakke.
Attributtet internal kan kun brukes i en pakke.
Et brukerdefinert navneområdeattributt kan kun brukes i toppnivået til en klassedefinisjon.

Implisitt tvang av en verdi med den statiske typen %s til en mulig urelatert type, %s. You are using a value that is not of the expected type and no implicit coercion exists to convert it to the expected type.

Perhaps you are using a supertype where a subtype is expected. For example: 

class A {}
var a:A = new A(); 
class B extends A { function f() }
var b : B = a // error

The last statement generates an error because it attempts to assign an object of type A to a variable of type B.

Similarly, the following defines the foo() function, which takes a parameter of type B. The statement foo(a); generates an error because it attempts to use a parameter of type A: 

function foo(x:B) { }
foo(a);

Also, the following statement generates an error because the returned value for foo2() must be type B: 

function foo2():B { return new A(); }

Tilgang til den mulig udefinerte egenskapen %s via en referanse med statisk type %s. You are attempting to access a property that does not exist for the specified object. For example, the following code generates this error because an int object does not have a property named assortment: 
var i:int = 44;
var str:String = i.assortment;
This error appears only when the compiler is running in strict mode.

Tilgang til den udefinerte egenskapen %s. You are attempting to access an undefined variable. For example, if the variable huh has not been defined, a call to it generates this error: 
huh = 55;
This error can appear only when the compiler is running in strict mode.
En getter-definisjon kan ikke ha noen parametere.
En setter-definisjon må ha én enkelt parameter.
En setter-definisjon kan ikke ha valgfrie parametere.

Returtypen til en getter-definisjon kan ikke være tom.
A getter function simulates a variable. Because variables cannot be of type void, you cannot declare getter functions to return type void.
Metoder som er definert i et grensesnitt, kan ikke ha en kropp.
Funksjonen har ikke en kropp.

Attributtet %s ble spesifisert flere ganger. You specified an attribute more than once in the same statement. For example, the statement public static public var x; generates this error because it specifies that the variable x is public twice. Delete duplicate declarations.

Change or delete the duplicate definitions.

{ return(x+y); } }

The following statement would generate an error because it provides three arguments:

The initializer of a configuration value must be a value known at compile time. The initializer may be a constant string, number, or boolean, or a reference to another previously defined configuration value.
